\#\# Phase 7: Alpha Testing

\#\#\# \*\*Step 7.1: Testing Protocol\*\*

\*\*Recruit 5-10 alpha users:\*\*  
\- Mix of stages (Rising, Thriving, Driving)  
\- Give them specific prompts to test  
\- Collect qualitative feedback

\*\*Test prompts:\*\*  
1\. "What should I prioritize this quarter?"  
2\. "Why do I feel stuck at $2M?"  
3\. "Is 60% client concentration too high?"  
4\. "What if I raise prices 15%?"  
5\. "How am I doing on my Q2 goals?"

\*\*Feedback form:\*\*  
\- Did responses feel relevant to YOUR business? (1-5)  
\- Did the system understand follow-up questions? (Y/N)  
\- Any responses that felt "off" or wrong? (Open text)  
\- What would make this more useful? (Open text)

\*\*Monitor during testing:\*\*  
\- Error logs (check daily)  
\- Routing decisions (are classifications correct?)  
\- Retrieval quality (are relevant chunks surfacing?)  
\- Response times (\>5s is problem)

\#\#\# \*\*Step 7.2: Iteration Based on Feedback\*\*

\*\*Common issues and fixes:\*\*

\*\*Issue: Generic responses\*\*  
\- Fix: Improve Agent 2's user data queries (pulling wrong context)  
\- Fix: Add more specific chunks to knowledge base

\*\*Issue: Wrong stage advice\*\*  
\- Fix: Agent 1 not passing stage correctly  
\- Fix: RAG results not filtering by stage properly

\*\*Issue: Doesn't remember conversation\*\*  
\- Fix: Session history not being passed correctly  
\- Fix: Agent 1 incorrectly flagging follow-ups as new topics

\*\*Issue: Slow responses\*\*  
\- Fix: Optimize SQL queries (add indexes)  
\- Fix: Reduce max\_chunks in Agent 1 prescriptions  
\- Fix: Consider caching user\_stage (it rarely changes)

