\#\# Critical Success Factors

1\. \*\*Test each agent standalone before connecting them\*\*  
   \- Debugging 3 connected workflows is 10x harder than debugging 1

2\. \*\*Use real data for testing\*\*  
   \- Don't test with "lorem ipsum" \- use actual chunks from your knowledge base

3\. \*\*Log everything initially\*\*  
   \- You'll need logs to understand why routing/retrieval isn't working

4\. \*\*Start with simple queries\*\*  
   \- Don't test with "explain the relationship between positioning, margins, and client concentration across 5 dimensions" on day 1  
   \- Start with "what is the 3P framework"

5\. \*\*Review Agent 3 responses manually\*\*  
   \- First 50-100 conversations should be reviewed by you  
   \- Look for hallucinations, wrong tone, irrelevant chunks being used

